comments: Embiid (PHI) briefly rests his right hand on Jaquez Jr.'s (MIA) side and the contact off-ball is marginal.
Adebayo (MIA) legally contests Batum's (PHI) jump shot attempt.
Embiid (PHI) momentarily rests and removes his hand from Jaquez Jr.'s (MIA) shoulder before elevating to pursue the rebound and the contact is marginal.
Highsmith (MIA) swipes his hand down at the ball and makes contact with Embiid's (PHI) right arm, which alters Embiid's upward shooting motion.
Adebayo (MIA) is firming up over his right leg as Maxey (PHI) attempts to defend over the pick and marginal contact occurs as the two players briefly come together.
Highsmith (MIA) moves alongside Embiid's (PHI) path and he absorbs the marginal contact as Embiid leans backward during the release of his driving shot attempt.
Adebayo (MIA) momentarily rests and removes his left hand from Embiid's (PHI) side as he aligns along Embiid's path and the contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.

Adebayo (MIA) establishes a legal position in Batum's (PHI) path before the contact. Batum reaches around Adebayo and makes contact to Herro's (MIA) side/arm as he is gathering the ball to end his dribble. The play-by-play incorrectly lists Adebayo as the player drawing the foul.
Batum (PHI) rests and removes his hand from Herro's (MIA) back as Herro moves to retrieve the ball and the touch contact is marginal.
Herro's (MIA) right foot comes down onto the half-court line while he is in contact with the ball. Possession is properly awarded to Philadelphia.
Butler (MIA) swipes his left arm down at the ball and leans slightly into Oubre Jr.'s (PHI) space when contact occurs with Oubre Jr.'s left arm, which alters his layup attempt at the basket.
Adebayo's (MIA) forearms briefly come out and rest on Batum's (PHI) side as Adebayo firms up in the defender's path and Adebayo does not deliver any illegal contact when setting the pick.

Batum (PHI) brings his right hand toward the ball and makes contact with it, legally blocking Herro's (MIA) jump shot attempt. After the contact with the ball, Batum's hand continues to follow-through when incidental contact occurs with Herro's wrist.

Highsmith (MIA) jumps into Maxey (PHI) as both players elevate in pursuit of the loose ball and body contact occurs, which dislodges Maxey during the rebounding opportunity. Highsmith's contact with the ball is simultaneous to his contact with Maxey, which dislodges the defensive player in the air.

Maxey (PHI) jumps alongside Highsmith's (MIA) path when he grazes the side of Highsmith's head during his contest of the driving shot attempt. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Batum (PHI) requests and is granted a timeout within five seconds of receiving the ball from the official.
Batum (PHI) releases his inbounds pass before five seconds have passed after receiving the ball from the official.
As Martin (MIA) defends over the screen, he comes together with Lowry (PHI) and marginal contact occurs. Lowry loses his balance on his own accord and falls to the floor.
Embiid (PHI) firms up over his right leg as Martin (MIA) moves towards the offensive player and the contact during the screen is marginal.
Embiid (PHI) raises his right arm up as he moves towards the ball during the inbounds and the contact with Adebayo (MIA) is marginal.
Martin (MIA) grabs and pulls the back of Lowry's (PHI) jersey as he retrieves the inbounds pass. Martin then extends his hand into the offensive player's back, which affects his SQBR.
Lowry (PHI) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes one legal step before releasing his pass and going to the floor.
Martin (MIA) jumps from point A to point B into Oubre Jr. (PHI), which impacts his layup attempt in the paint.
Lowry (PHI) legally contests Jaquez Jr.'s (MIA) jump shot attempt.
Highsmith (MIA) momentarily grasps and promptly releases the side of Maxey's (PHI) jersey during the inbound and the contact is marginal.
Highsmith (MIA) commits a take foul on Maxey (PHI). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.

Batum (PHI) brings both hands to Herro's (MIA) sides and the contact affects Herro's FOM as he attempts to move around the screen. The illegal contact occurs prior to the inbound pass being released and an away from the play foul is correctly called.
Love (MIA) firms up over his left leg and does not deliver any illegal contact to Lowry (PHI) when setting the screen.
Adebayo (MIA) turns slightly as he firms up over his left leg and marginal contact occurs with Lowry (PHI) as he comes together with Adebayo during the screen.
Lowry (PHI) legally contests Jaquez Jr.'s (MIA) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: The game clock expires prior to the ball, which was last touched by Embiid (PHI), bouncing out of bounds.
